The board of  Sterling Bank (STERLNBA)  Plc, a
Nigerian lender, will meet to decide on the size and timing of a
plan to raise capital, said Yemi Adeola, its managing director.  The bank plans to open seven new branches as it expands its
retail business, Adeola said in an interview today in Lagos, the
commercial capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
